Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.81,0:02:10.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Ahh! He's gonna eat me! - OG}Ahh! Vai me comer!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:10.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Take these! - OG}Toma essa!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.68,0:02:30.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Move! Move aside, Iceburg! - OG}Sai da frente, Iceburg!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:37.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bem...! Que droga está fazendo, Franky?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.97,0:02:44.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Idiota!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.59,0:02:44.18,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Ai!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:45.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bem...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.43,0:02:47.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What the hell are you doing\Ninstead of helping me with work?! - OG}{\q2}Que história é essa?! Por que não está me ajudando a trabalhar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.94,0:02:50.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think that you keep making unstable stuff like this! - OG}Só constrói essa porcaria perigosa!{JT/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:53.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\q2}{Shut up! It's none of your business, Stupid-berg! - OG}Cala a boca! Não é da sua conta, Iceburro!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:57.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is my precious battleship, the Battle Franky! - OG}Esse é meu navio de guerra favorito,\No {\i1}Battle Franky{\i0}!{Z/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.65,0:03:00.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't know what that is, but ditch the whole thing before someone gets hurt! - OG}Não me importa! Se livra disso\Nantes que alguém se machuque!{Z/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.97,0:03:04.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is the scrap heap island! It's my own business to keep whatever I want! - OG}Posso guardar o que quiser aqui!\NIsto é a Ilha do Ferro-Velho!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.28,0:03:08.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Just wait and see! Next time for sure, I'll build a battleship that will beat sea kings! - OG}Espera e vê. Meu próximo navio de guerra\Nvai acabar com aqueles monstros marinhos!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:10.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well...! There's no way you can beat them! I hope you get eaten! - OG}Bom, impossível! Vai virar comida de monstro!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.83,0:03:12.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can beat them! - OG}Vou sim!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.58,0:03:12.71,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well...! You can't! - OG}Bom, não vai!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.71,0:03:14.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can! - OG}Vou sim!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:14.82,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well...! You can't! - OG}Bom, não vai!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.67,0:03:23.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\bord2.9\shad2\fnFOT-Greco Std B Strp\fscx92\fscy92\b1}{If you're a man... do it resolutely! - OG}♪ Um homem dá tudo de si, {\i1}pô{\i0}! ♪{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.84,0:03:43.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That concludes the launch ceremony! - OG}Isso conclui a cerimônia de lançamento!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.27,0:03:46.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We were resolutely able to make a solid, good ship! - OG}Construímos um navio firme e {\i1}super{\i0} resistente.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.74,0:03:48.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Right, Yokozuna? - OG}Não foi, Yokozuna?{Z}
Comment: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:48.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.55,0:03:52.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Let's finish it up tomorrow, shall we? - OG}Que tal terminarmos amanhã?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:54.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, let's go home. - OG}Vamos pra casa.{Z}
Comment: 0,0:03:53.65,0:03:54.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.05,0:03:57.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Boy, I'm hungry. - OG}Ah, estou morrendo de fome.{Z}
Comment: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:57.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.43,0:03:59.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I wonder what we're having for dinner. - OG}O que será que tem pra janta.{Gaijin}
Comment: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:00.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.48,0:04:01.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.29,0:04:03.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Wait, Tom-[/i1]san[/i0]!}– Espera, Tom!\N– Espera, Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.38,0:04:15.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So which Battle Franky did you build this time, Franky? - OG}Então, em que número está\No seu {\i1}Battle Franky{\i0} agora?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.06,0:04:16.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The eighth one. - OG}Ah, está no oito.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.11,0:04:17.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It was close! - OG}Dessa vez quase deu!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.69,0:04:18.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't lie! - OG}Mentiroso!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.75,0:04:21.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Geez... Since you let him do this stuff, Tom-san, he gets full of himself! - OG}Puxa, sua tolerância só deixa\Nele mais folgado, Tom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.63,0:04:23.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tudo que ele faz são armas!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.49,0:04:25.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Shut up, Stupid-berg! - OG}Cala a boca, Iceburro!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:29.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What'd you say, Moron-ky?! - OG}O que disse, Franburro?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.58,0:04:33.42,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{Moron... ky! - OG}Fran... burro!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:35.80,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{He said "Moron-ky"! - OG}E-Ele me chamou de "Franburro"!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:35.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, now, stop fighting, both of you. - OG}Pronto, pronto... Parem de brigar, vocês dois.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.80,0:04:38.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{– But Kokoro-[/i1]san[/i0]! This idiot was...!\N– But Kokoro-[/i1]san[/i0]! This idiot was...! - OG}– Mas dona Kokoro, esse idiota é que...!\N– Mas dona Kokoro, esse idiota é que...!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:41.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Geez... - OG}Meu Deus...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.02,0:04:43.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\q2}{You too, Tom-san. You're laughing too hard. - OG}E chega de rir, Tom.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.07,0:04:45.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What was so funny? - OG}Que bicho te mordeu?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:48.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh... yea... I just remembered. - OG}Ah, a propósito,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.00,0:04:51.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I heard that another trading ship with lumber on it was attacked by pirates. - OG}ouvi que piratas atacaram outro navio de carga com madeira.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.88,0:04:55.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{After the King of the Pirates was executed, the number of pirates grew considerably. - OG}Desde a execução do Rei dos Piratas,\No número de piratas cresceu muito.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:59.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's all over for this town. It's being\Novertaken by the pirate era. - OG}Nossa cidade está quase acabada.\NA era pirata nos engoliu.{Gaijin/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.96,0:05:02.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{People are in low spirits. - OG}Parece que não tem esperança.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.02,0:05:09.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We can now get lumber and iron only from other islands due to the floods caused by Aqua Laguna, - OG}As enchentes da Aqua Laguna nos obrigam a buscar\Nmadeira e ferro em outras ilhas,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.12,0:05:12.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{and yet, violent seas and pirates hinder trading. - OG}mas mares traiçoeiros\Ne piratas atrapalham o comércio.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:16.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Shipyards scramble for customers due to the shortage of work. - OG}A falta de trabalho faz\Nos estaleiros brigarem por clientes.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.41,0:05:19.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They start fighting. They lose their jobs. - OG}Surgem brigas e as pessoas perdem seus empregos.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.07,0:05:25.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If nothing is done, Water Seven, an island that once left its mark with its shipbuilding business, - OG}Se nada for feito, Water 7, uma ilha\Noutrora renomada pela construção naval...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.46,0:05:32.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{will become weak-minded,\Njust waiting for floods to happen. - OG}vai se acomodar, apenas esperando\Na enchente engolir tudo.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.38,0:05:36.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's right! Tom-san built an incredible pirate ship, too! - OG}É verdade! O Tom construiu\Naquele navio pirata incrível!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.56,0:05:38.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Say, teach me how to draw blueprints for a pirate ship! - OG}Ei, me mostra plantas de um navio pirata!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:44.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's so funny? - OG}Por que está rindo?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:49.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Franky, não existe planta\Nde navio pirata.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:53.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If the sailors who board a ship put up\Na skull flag, then it's a pirate ship. - OG}Se os marinheiros hasteiam uma bandeira\Nde caveira, é um navio pirata.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.37,0:05:55.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If they put up a seagull flag, then it's a Navy ship. - OG}Navios da Marinha usam uma bandeira de gaivota.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:59.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't care what you wanna build, - OG}Não importa o que ele queira construir,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:04.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but a man should be resolutely proud of the ship he built. - OG}mas um homem deve ter {\i1}muito{\i0} orgulho\Ndo navio que constrói!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:10.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Aren't you going to bed yet, Tom-san? - OG}Não vai dormir, Tom?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.49,0:06:12.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que está desenhando?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.88,0:06:16.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Mm... It's this island's hope. - OG}Ah... Isso é a esperança da ilha.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:18.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esperança?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.42,0:06:22.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hopefully, it can revive Water Seven. - OG}Essa ideia pode revitalizar Water 7.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.20,0:06:24.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, go to bed. - OG}Agora, vai dormir.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.41,0:06:26.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah. - OG}Tá bom.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.95,0:06:27.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Comment: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:42.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.85,0:06:49.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The government's judicial ship is here! - OG}O navio judicial do governo está aqui!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.05,0:06:51.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que é um navio judicial?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:52.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's a mobile court. - OG}É um tribunal móvel.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:54.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Who did they come to judge? - OG}E quem vai ser julgado?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:07:00.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Wait a sec! - OG}Espera aí!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.55,0:07:02.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What did Tom-san do to deserve this?! Hey! Outta my way, you jerks! - OG}O que o Tom fez pra merecer isso?\NSaiam da frente, seus idiotas!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.93,0:07:04.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Give us Tom-san back! - OG}Devolvam o Tom, seus idiotas!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.52,0:07:08.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll be fine. Don't worry. - OG}Vai ficar tudo bem. Não se preocupe.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.20,0:07:15.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom-[/i1]san[/i0]! Tom-[/i1]san[/i0]! - OG}Tom! Tom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.87,0:07:26.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, was executed the other day. - OG}Gold Roger, o Rei dos Piratas,\Nfoi recentemente executado.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.47,0:07:29.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We consider shipbuilding engineer Tom's\Nact of building Gold Roger's pirate ship, - OG}Ao construir o navio de Gold Roger,\No {\i1}Oro Jackson{\i0},{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.47,0:07:32.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{[/q2] - the Oro Jackson, to be aiding and abetting this vicious world-class criminal! - OG}o carpinteiro Tom auxiliou\Ne incentivou este criminoso!{Z}
Comment: 0,0:07:29.14,0:07:30.54,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Hurry!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.45,0:07:38.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hence, Tom will be taken to Enies Lobby to be executed! - OG}Por este crime de nível mundial, Tom será levado\Na Enies Lobby onde será executado!{Z/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:40.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O quê?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.02,0:07:44.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is terrible! Tom will... Tom will be executed! - OG}Notícia terrível! Tom...\NTom foi condenado à morte!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.64,0:07:48.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They say it's on the charge of building the King of the Pirates' ship. - OG}Dizem que construir o navio\Ndo Rei dos Piratas é crime.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.53,0:07:49.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So it's finally time, huh? - OG}Finalmente aconteceu.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.65,0:07:52.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It caused problems for the entire world. They had no choice. - OG}Causou problemas pro mundo inteiro.\NEle mereceu.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.41,0:07:59.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Normally, no matter whom a shipwright sells a ship to, it's not a crime. - OG}Normalmente, não seria crime para\Num carpinteiro vender seu navio a quem quer que seja.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.09,0:08:01.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{However, the King of the Pirates is an exception. - OG}No entanto, o Rei dos Piratas\Né uma exceção.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.37,0:08:07.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We consider all those who have assisted in his pirating activities to be dangerous individuals! - OG}Qualquer pessoa considerada envolvida\Ncom sua pirataria é um perigo para o mundo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.85,0:08:09.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hence, he's sentenced to the death penalty! - OG}Portanto, eu o condeno à morte!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.56,0:08:11.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Take the offender away. - OG}Levem o condenado!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:11.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{– Yes, sir!\N– Yes, sir! - OG}– Sim, Meritíssimo!\N– Sim, Meritíssimo!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:13.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, let's go. - OG}Vamos.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.22,0:08:14.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hurry up and walk! - OG}Ande logo!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:16.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's the matter? - OG}Vamos...!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.10,0:08:17.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go already! - OG}Ande!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.61,0:08:19.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey, what're you doing?! - OG}Ei, o que está fazendo?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.01,0:08:20.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Estou atualmente projetando...{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.46,0:08:20.77,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Hã?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.18,0:08:26.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{a paddle steamer that resolutely runs on a railway set on the ocean's surface. - OG}um navio a vapor com pás que vai\Ncorrer sobre trilhos no oceano.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.65,0:08:29.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey! What're you saying?! - OG}Ei, você! Não fale com ele!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:30.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why, you...! - OG}Sai...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.57,0:08:36.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Suppose this island's decline is due to trade not happening as we wish it... - OG}Enquanto falamos, esta ilha decai\Ndevido ao comércio estagnado.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.67,0:08:37.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Suppose - OG}Enquanto falamos,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:44.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{the hopelessness that people feel is coming from the worries about this sinking island... - OG}o povo está desmoralizado\Npelo medo de que a ilha afunde.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:46.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Putting a sea train into operation... - OG}Colocar um sea train em operação...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.55,0:08:51.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{will definitely save Water Seven someday! - OG}vai definitivamente salvar nossa ilha, Water 7!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.38,0:08:55.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I-I'm sorry! We will take him out right away! - OG}D-Desculpe.\NVamos removê-lo imediatamente.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.82,0:08:57.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não, espere um momento.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.31,0:08:57.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{– Huh?\N– Huh? - OG}– O quê?\N– O quê?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.93,0:09:00.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Sea train, you said? - OG}Você disse... "um sea train"?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:06.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's a ship that puffs smoke and runs from one island to another on a sea railway. - OG}É um navio que solta fumaça e corre sobre trilhos\Nno mar, de uma ilha pra outra.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.77,0:09:11.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll carry people and goods as well as ships. Without having to worry about the weather, - OG}Carregando passageiros, mercadorias e outros navios\Nsem se preocupar com o clima,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:15.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,todos poderão cruzar o oceano livremente.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.17,0:09:16.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Stop kidding yourself! - OG}Bom demais pra ser verdade.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:20.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{A railway? It'd be destroyed once Aqua Laguna comes! - OG}Trilhos? Seriam destruídos\Nna primeira Aqua Laguna!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.82,0:09:24.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's right! Besides, there are also sea kings in the sea! - OG}É verdade! E não vamos esquecer dos monstros marinhos!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:27.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The sea railway doesn't have to be fixed. - OG}Trilhos no mar não precisariam ser fixos.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.23,0:09:33.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll sway a little below the surface of the water, never resisting the waves. - OG}Balançando logo abaixo da superfície\Nda água, sem nunca resistir à maré.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.09,0:09:38.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{As if pulling in a rope, the sea train will just use the railway as a guide. - OG}Como puxando uma corda, o sea train\Nusará os trilhos apenas como guia.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.26,0:09:40.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Furthermore, I'm thinking of adding a mechanism - OG}Além disso, vou adicionar um mecanismo{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.62,0:09:45.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{a discordant sound that fish hate between the paddles and the railway. - OG}entre as pás e os trilhos que cria um som\Ndiscordante para afastar peixes.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.98,0:09:50.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then sea kings won't come close to the railway. - OG}Assim os monstros marinhos\Nnão chegarão perto dos trilhos.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:51.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is something like that possible? - OG}Algo assim funcionaria?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.54,0:09:56.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If we connect St. Poplar, Pucci, San Faldo, and this island, - OG}Conectando Saint Poplar, Pucci,\NSan Faldo e esta ilha,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:10:00.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{industries can grow through trading. - OG}podemos desenvolver nossas indústrias\Natravés do comércio mútuo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:01.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How wonderful...! - OG}Incrível...!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:07.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The blueprints will be completed soon, but it's not so simple that ordinary shipwrights can build it. - OG}Devo terminar as plantas em breve,\Nmas não é trabalho pra qualquer carpinteiro.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:10.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is it possible to connect Enies Lobby as well? - OG}E uma parada em Enies Lobby?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.17,0:10:12.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Of course it is! - OG}Sem problema!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:18.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Once this technology is completed and eventually crosses the ocean - OG}Quando essa tecnologia for completada\Ne se espalhar pelos mares,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:21.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{the relationships among islands all around the world will resolutely change! - OG}vai mudar {\i1}completamente{\i0} as relações\Nentre as ilhas do mundo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:25.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O sea train é a esperança de Water 7!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.35,0:10:27.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quanto tempo vai levar?{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.81,0:10:29.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Dez anos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:30.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Então construa!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.98,0:10:33.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{As the development period for the sea train, - OG}Tom, o carpinteiro,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.06,0:10:38.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I give ten years probation to shipbuilding engineer Tom! - OG}eu lhe concedo uma prorrogação de dez anos\Npara desenvolver o sea train!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:41.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é incrível!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.56,0:10:43.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Good luck, Tom! - OG}Vamos lá, Tom!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.45,0:10:46.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Please save Water Seven! - OG}Salve Water 7!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.37,0:10:51.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm resolutely still alive! - OG}Ainda estou {\i1}muito{\i0} vivo!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.54,0:10:54.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is no laughing matter, Tom-san. - OG}Isso não é motivo de riso, Tom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:57.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I thought that your time had come and a chill ran down my spine. - OG}Um arrepio percorreu minha espinha\Nao pensar no que estava por vir.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:02.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But anyway, if things go well, they may let the matter with Roger go, huh? - OG}Mas agora, se tudo der certo,\Neles podem retirar as acusações sobre Roger.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.18,0:11:05.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well...! At any rate, you're great, Tom-san! - OG}Bom...! Tenho que admitir, você é incrível, Tom!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.56,0:11:09.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think you've been thinking about something like that! Everyone was overwhelmed! - OG}Tinha essa grande ideia guardada\Ne impressionou todo mundo!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.27,0:11:10.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The sea train really is... - OG}O sea train realmente–{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:12.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Thanks for the dinner! - OG}Valeu pela comida!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.39,0:11:14.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Come, Yokozuna! I'll teach you how to do the front crawl! - OG}Yokozuna, vou te ensinar o nado crawl.{Gaijin}
Comment: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:15.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:18.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey, Franky! What's with you?! You've been sulking for awhile now! - OG}Ei, que foi, Franky?!\NVocê tá emburrado desde que chegamos.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.99,0:11:22.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Shut up! I'm angry at everything! - OG}Cala a boca! Tô puto com tudo!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:26.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Gold Roger's ship is the only ship in the world that went around the Grand Line! - OG}O navio de Gold Roger é o único no mundo\Nque deu a volta na Grand Line!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.48,0:11:29.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why does Tom-san, who built such a great ship, have to get executed?! - OG}Por que o Tom precisa ser executado\Npor construir um navio tão incrível?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:32.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The people there were also saying that it was just natural, - OG}Os curiosos ficaram agindo\Ncomo se fosse óbvio,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.83,0:11:34.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{even though those idiots can't even build a raft! - OG}mas aqueles idiotas\Nnem conseguem construir uma jangada!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.92,0:11:36.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I also know that - OG}Eu também sei o que está acontecendo!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:41.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{the reason our company is under a bridge is because you were kicked out by the townspeople over Roger's ship, right?! - OG}{\q2}Nossa empresa fica debaixo de uma ponte porque a cidade\Nte expulsou por causa do navio do Roger, não é?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.26,0:11:45.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why the hell does the world's best shipwright have to be treated like this?! - OG}Por que o melhor carpinteiro do mundo\Ntem que passar por isso?!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.14,0:11:49.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's funny, you horned raccoon dog?! - OG}Que foi de engraçado, seu {\i1}tanuki{\i0} chifrudo?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.54,0:11:52.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Who're you taking it out on, Moron-ky?! You are not gonna get away with it! - OG}Sai de cima dele, Franburro! Não vou permitir!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.02,0:11:53.94,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't stand that the person himself is like that, either! - OG}E eu não vou permitir que ele morra!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.61,0:12:00.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No, no! That's not it! - OG}Não, não! Tá tudo errado!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:03.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Stroke with all your might to push the water backwards! - OG}Empurra a água pra trás com toda força!{Gaijin}
Comment: 0,0:12:04.45,0:12:06.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ribbit! Ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:09.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No! No! Stroke more vigorously like this! - OG}Não, não é isso! Tem que braçar mais forte!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.70,0:12:11.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Seriously, what's with him?! - OG}Sério, qual é o problema dele?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.21,0:12:11.80,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Não! Assim!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.80,0:12:13.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You should just kick out an idiot like him! - OG}Devia simplesmente expulsar esse idiota!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.79,0:12:17.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, don't say that. He's a fellow shipbuilder. - OG}Bom, não diga isso.\NEle é um carpinteiro como você e eu.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:22.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In terms of shipbuilding skills, there's already no big difference between him and the craftsmen on the island... - OG}Em habilidade, ele já está quase\Nno nível dos outros carpinteiros da ilha.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.30,0:12:24.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{though what he makes is shaky. - OG}Porém, as criações dele são meio perigosas.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.55,0:12:28.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He's just always honest, that's all. - OG}Ele é simplesmente sempre honesto.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.89,0:12:37.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Two years ago, when I saw a kid who had resolutely appeared on the scrap heap island - OG}Esse garoto apareceu na Ilha do Ferro-Velho\Nhá dois anos,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.52,0:12:40.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{make a cannon using junk, I was really surprised. - OG}e pra minha surpresa tinha\Nconstruído um canhão de sucata.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.24,0:12:45.36,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Old man, take me in! I was abandoned by my parents! - OG}Ei, véio, me acolhe! Meus pais me largaram!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.70,0:12:50.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He told me that his parents said, "What an uncontrollable brat," and threw him off the ship. - OG}Ele disse que os pais o jogaram do navio\Nporque não conseguiam controlá-lo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.97,0:12:54.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It seems that they were worthless pirates from some place, though. - OG}Parece que eram piratas,\Nmas dos ruins, sabe?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.20,0:12:57.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That was so funny! - OG}Foi hilário!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:57.08,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom-san... - OG}Tom...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.08,0:12:59.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He's tough, isn't he? - OG}Ele é forte, não acha?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:02.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Despite his circumstances, he isn't crooked. - OG}Apesar das circunstâncias, é um bom garoto.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:07.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You two will definitely become world-class\Nshipbuilding engineers someday. - OG}Vocês dois serão carpinteiros\Nde nível mundial algum dia.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.22,0:13:09.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You should be nice to each other. - OG}Se deem bem um com o outro.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.04,0:13:12.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Franky can't do it. He's crazy\Neven at the cellular level! - OG}Impossível com o Franky.\NCada fibra dele é maluca.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.94,0:13:18.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, as soon as I finish the blueprints,\Nwe'll start building the sea train! - OG}Enfim, assim que terminar as plantas,\Nvamos começar a construir o sea train!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.04,0:13:21.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah... but I bet he won't help us. - OG}Tá. Mas duvido que ele ajude.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.07,0:13:25.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He can do as he pleases! - OG}Ele que faça o que quiser!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.69,0:15:02.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Suicídio?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.84,0:15:06.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I heard that it was the president\Nof the No. 4 shipbuilding company. - OG}Ouvi que era o presidente da\Nempresa de construção naval da doca quatro.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.55,0:15:07.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It must be because of that accident. - OG}Deve ter sido por causa do acidente...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.54,0:15:12.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since they didn't have materials, he went\Nto purchase lumber on his own ship - OG}Ele saiu com o próprio navio\Npra comprar madeira, pois estavam sem,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.42,0:15:14.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{and got fifty people killed on the sea. - OG}e cinquenta pessoas morreram no mar.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.19,0:15:17.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{His shipyard is closed, too. - OG}O estaleiro dele também vai fechar.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.43,0:15:20.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How weak humans are, huh? - OG}As pessoas são tão frágeis...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.46,0:15:24.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is this really it for this island? - OG}Será que essa ilha já era?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.31,0:15:25.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.86,0:15:29.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Did you guys hear\Nabout the scrap heap island?! - OG}Vocês souberam da Ilha do Ferro-Velho?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.55,0:15:32.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,E-Ei, é verdade?!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.99,0:15:36.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom's Workers has finished\Nbuilding the sea train, you say?! - OG}Está dizendo que a Tom's Workers\Nterminou o sea train?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:39.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Whoa! Does a ship like this really run? - OG}Uau! Esse navio realmente funciona?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.91,0:15:42.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's a ship built by a criminal. It's dangerous! - OG}Deve ser perigoso. Foi feito por um criminoso.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.75,0:15:44.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll get on board! - OG}Quero ir.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.15,0:15:45.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Me too, then. - OG}Então... acho que eu também.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.29,0:15:46.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom! You are not gonna explain?! - OG}Tom, vai nos explicar?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.96,0:15:49.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're leaving! Get on board! - OG}Estamos partindo. Todos a bordo!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.26,0:15:57.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Está se movendo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.55,0:16:00.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,As pás estão agarrando nos trilhos!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:02.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Está se movendo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:04.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Whoa, amazing! It's running! - OG}Uau! Olha ele ir!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.21,0:16:18.42,Narrator-207+,,0,0,0,,Doze anos atrás...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.42,0:16:25.04,Narrator-207+,,0,0,0,,{...leaving a closed, declining town, with worried people on board... - OG}partindo de uma cidade isolada e em declínio\Ncom pessoas ansiosas a bordo...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.01,0:16:34.59,Narrator-207+,,0,0,0,,o sea train Puffing Tom cruzou\No mar pela primeira vez.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.27,0:16:44.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Entendo...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.98,0:16:52.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So this filthy warehouse used to be Tom's Workers shipbuilding company's main office, huh? - OG}{\q2}Então esse armazém sujo era a sede da empresa\Nde construção naval Tom's Workers, né?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.78,0:16:54.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uma empresa de construção naval?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.04,0:16:59.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tom, Iceburg e Cutty Flam...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.10,0:17:04.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So this is a place that holds memories of the three of you devoting yourselves to building ships, huh?- OG}Esse lugar guarda memórias\Nde vocês três construindo navios, certo?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.17,0:17:10.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think that you call it a secret base... That's quite adorable. - OG}Chamar de "base secreta"\Né bem fofo da sua parte.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.67,0:17:12.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Shut up! - OG}Cala a boca!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.55,0:17:14.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Get out of this place already! - OG}Saiam logo daqui!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:19.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Not until we get what we want,\Nshipwright Cutty Flam. - OG}Iremos quando conseguirmos o que viemos buscar...\Ncarpinteiro Cutty Flam.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.80,0:17:21.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The blueprints are not here! - OG}Não tem planta nenhuma aqui!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.77,0:17:26.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well... That's not surprising. - OG}Bom, era a resposta esperada.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.52,0:17:28.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.19,0:17:29.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Kalifa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.37,0:17:34.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ai...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:40.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Q-Q-Q-Que faço?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:45.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Seu desgraçado...!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.32,0:17:49.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You don't have to tell us right away. - OG}Temos tempo de sobra\Npra arrancar a verdade de você.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.84,0:17:52.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We've got a trump card. - OG}Temos uma carta na manga.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.55,0:17:55.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Although this is from eight years ago, - OG}Pode ter sido há oito anos,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.25,0:17:58.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I heard that you committed a crime... - OG}mas parece que você também\Né culpado de alguns crimes...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.76,0:18:00.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{...just like Tom did. - OG}assim como o Tom.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.43,0:18:03.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's a load of crap! Tom-san wasn't a criminal! - OG}Que besteira! O Tom não era criminoso!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:05.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't talk like you know everything! - OG}Não fale como se soubesse de tudo,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.89,0:18:07.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{ You brat! - OG}seu moleque!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.06,0:18:18.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom-san...! - OG}Tom...!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.69,0:18:21.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Stay back! - OG}Fique aí!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.45,0:18:23.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't make a fuss. - OG}Calma.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.99,0:18:29.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're a criminal. You should\Nknow what will happen to you. - OG}Como criminoso, deveria saber\Nas consequências dos seus atos.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.66,0:18:31.54,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Franky...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.05,0:18:34.76,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't interfere\Nin what I'm about to do... - OG}não interfira no que vou fazer agora...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.76,0:18:36.18,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{No matter what. - OG}não importa o quê!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.74,0:18:38.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You don't know anything... - OG}Vocês não sabem nada...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:41.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Anything about Tom-san... - OG}nada sobre o Tom...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:47.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Anything about Water Seven! - OG}{\i1}nem{\i0} sobre Water 7!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.55,0:19:00.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The Judicial Ship is coming in three days? - OG}O navio judicial chega em três dias?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:03.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They're finally having Tom's trial, huh? - OG}Ah, o julgamento do Tom, né?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.08,0:19:04.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I wonder what'll happen? - OG}Como será que vai ser.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:06.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He should be okay. - OG}Ele deve ficar bem.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.58,0:19:07.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah. - OG}Com certeza.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:10.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He did fulfill his promise. - OG}Afinal, ele cumpriu a promessa.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.60,0:19:11.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah. - OG}Sem dúvida.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:17.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Carry the received lumber into the dock! - OG}Levem essa carga pra doca.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.79,0:19:20.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Did the negotiation in St. Poplar go well? - OG}Como foram as negociações com Saint Poplar?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.55,0:19:22.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Not yet. - OG}Não foi bem.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:25.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They're taking advantage\Nof us since we don't have materials. - OG}Estão se aproveitando\Nda nossa falta de recursos.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.44,0:19:27.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It was the same deal with the iron in San Faldo! - OG}A mesma coisa com o ferro de San Faldo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.31,0:19:30.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Shipyards will end up going into\Nthe red if things are that expensive! - OG}Com preços assim, os estaleiros\Nvão ficar no vermelho!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.27,0:19:33.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Mas na próxima a gente resolve!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.66,0:19:35.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– É! Isso mesmo!\N– É! Isso mesmo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.12,0:19:44.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Everyone is happy about\Nbeing able to cross the ocean, - OG}Todo mundo está feliz por poder\Nviajar pras outras ilhas...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.41,0:19:47.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but I heard that trading with\Nother islands isn't going well. - OG}mas o comércio com elas parece complicado.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.18,0:19:50.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I wonder if the town won't\Nchange even with the sea train... - OG}O sea train não mudou muito a cidade...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:55.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But people are lively! - OG}Pelo menos o povo está animado.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.37,0:19:58.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The results won't show immediately, Iceburg. - OG}Resultados não aparecem da noite pro dia, Iceburg.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.55,0:20:03.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Once a man's done everything he could, he should just resolutely keep his head high! - OG}Quando um homem faz tudo que pode,\Ndeve manter a cabeça erguida com {\i1}orgulho{\i0}!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:04.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah. - OG}Tá bom.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.49,0:20:16.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hello there. - OG}Olá e bom dia, senhor.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.20,0:20:19.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Are you Mr. Tom,\Na shipbuilding engineer? - OG}O senhor é o mestre\Ncarpinteiro Tom?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.81,0:20:22.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, I've been looking all over for you. - OG}Ah, como procurei pelo senhor!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.11,0:20:23.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.32,0:20:26.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Excuse me, but I'd like to... - OG}Com licença, mas tenho um assunto pra–{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.55,0:20:26.20,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Um... - OG}Hm...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.20,0:20:28.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't interrupt! Step back! - OG}Não me interrompam! Afastem-se!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.14,0:20:28.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Sim, senhor!\N– Sim, senhor!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.75,0:20:31.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'd like to have a little conversation with... - OG}Tenho um assunto pra dis–{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.75,0:20:38.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,E-Eu sou...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.43,0:20:41.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{...from Cipher Pol No. 5. - OG}da Cipher Pol Número 5...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.66,0:20:43.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm Spand... - OG}Spandam!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.18,0:20:44.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Spandam-san! - OG}– Agente Spandam!\N– Agente Spandam!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:49.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh, sorry! - OG}Ah! Desculpa!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.72,0:20:53.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't know who you are,\Nbut my cannon salute hit you! - OG}Não sei quem você é,\Nmas parece que minha salva de canhão te acertou.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.19,0:20:54.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And... - OG}E mais...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.11,0:21:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{...this is super! The Battle\NFranky No. 35 has returned! - OG}Estou super! O {\i1}Battle Franky 35{\i0} voltou!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.00,0:21:01.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu matei um monstro marinho!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.82,0:21:05.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Look at this size! It's a monster\Nthat must be at least 100m in length! - OG}Olha o tamanho! Esse monstro tem\Npelo menos 100 metros de comprimento!{Z/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.99,0:21:10.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esse idiota... Nunca aprende.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.57,0:21:16.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Ahhh, you bastard! Stop it, Stupid-berg! - OG}Ahh, seu desgraçado! Para com isso, Iceburro!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:19.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How many times do I have to tell you?! - OG}Quando você vai aprender?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.01,0:21:22.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think that you keep building\Nstupid battleships one after another! - OG}Fica construindo esses malditos\Nnavios de guerra sem parar!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.63,0:21:24.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Enough is enough! - OG}Já chega!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.09,0:21:28.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you can't, I'll destroy all\Nof them today for sure! - OG}Se não consegue parar, então hoje é o dia\Nque eu desmonto eles por você!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.24,0:21:29.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't you dare! - OG}Não se atreva!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.01,0:21:30.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,São meus preciosos navios de guerra!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.98,0:21:33.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I won't let you mess with my ships! - OG}De jeito nenhum que vou deixar!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.55,0:21:35.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom...! Escuta aqui, Franky!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.48,0:21:38.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você matou um monstro marinho, certo?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.08,0:21:40.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That means that this is quite a lethal weapon! - OG}Isso significa que isso é uma arma letal.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.11,0:21:44.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't understand your nerve,\Njust leaving dozens of them out here! - OG}Não entendo como você pode deixar\Ndezenas dessas coisas espalhadas por aí.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.19,0:21:47.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's not like I'm gonna attack people with them! - OG}Não é como se eu fosse\Natacar pessoas com elas!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.66,0:21:49.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It has nothing to do with your intention! - OG}Não é uma questão de intenção!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.73,0:21:52.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm calling you to account for\Ncreating lethal weapons, Moron-ky! - OG}Você é culpado por criar\Nessas armas, Franburro!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.88,0:21:55.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{E... Excuse m... - OG}E-Espera...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.62,0:22:00.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom-san! Please say something! - OG}Tom, fala alguma coisa!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.46,0:22:03.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Moron-ky is a disgrace to our company! - OG}Franburro é uma vergonha pra nossa empresa!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.05,0:22:04.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You said "Moron-ky" again! - OG}De novo com o "Franburro"!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.98,0:22:08.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{E-Excuse me... Please hold on a second! - OG}E-Espera só um minuto, por favor!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.43,0:22:13.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{First, I want you to apologize to me!\NAnd then, I want you to listen to me! - OG}Primeiro, quero um pedido de desculpas.\NDepois, quero que me ouçam!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.97,0:22:16.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're from the Government,\Naren't you? - OG}Você é do governo?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:18.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is it about the trial? - OG}É sobre meu julgamento?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.06,0:22:20.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What? What're you talking about? - OG}Hã? Do que está falando?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.90,0:22:24.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No, I don't know anything about it. - OG}Não, senhor, não sei nada sobre isso.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.03,0:22:25.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.36,0:22:29.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What happened to Tom-san? - OG}Cadê o Tom?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.87,0:22:32.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He said he wanted to talk alone. - OG}Eles quiseram conversar a sós.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.69,0:22:35.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He's with a man from the\NGovernment in the brick warehouse. - OG}Ele está no armazém de tijolos\Ncom um cara do governo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.80,0:22:38.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This guy's name is Span... What was that? - OG}Span... Como era mesmo?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:40.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's Spanda-something. - OG}Spanda... alguma coisa.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.08,0:22:43.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That official isn't from the Judicial Ship. - OG}Parece que não é do navio judicial.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.48,0:22:46.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What disorganized people... - OG}Não são muito organizados.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.07,0:22:52.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't know about it! I don't have\Nany blueprints for something like that! - OG}Não sei de nada! Não tenho\Nplanta nenhuma dessas!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.56,0:22:54.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't lie! - OG}Mentira!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.90,0:22:57.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think that you're playing innocent\Njust because I've been acting humble! - OG}Não abuse da minha humildade\Nse fazendo de desentendido!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.71,0:23:00.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We've already investigated by going\Nback into the history of Water Seven! - OG}Já investigamos todo o passado\Nde Water 7!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.90,0:23:04.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If we check your belongings, the actual\Narticle will show up in no time! - OG}Se revistarmos o local,\Nvamos encontrar num instante!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.88,0:23:09.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Do you guys have the\Nauthority to investigate me? - OG}Vocês sequer têm\Nautoridade pra me investigar?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.55,0:23:12.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We sure do, Tom! - OG}Pode apostar que sim, Tom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.69,0:23:18.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Believe it or not, our investigation already found out that you're a heinous criminal who built Gold Roger's ship. - OG}Eu já sei que você é o criminoso\Nque construiu o navio de Gold Roger!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.25,0:23:22.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since you're a criminal, we can\Ndo whatever we want with you. - OG}E como você é um criminoso,\Nseus direitos já não valem nada.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.56,0:23:25.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The Government already knows it. - OG}Ah, o governo já sabe\Nde tudo isso.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.60,0:23:26.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O quê?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.46,0:23:28.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Can't be! - OG}Isso é absurdo!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.47,0:23:32.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then why are you working here as a\Nshipwright instead of being in jail?! - OG}Então por que está livre trabalhando como\Ncarpinteiro em vez de estar numa cela?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.93,0:23:36.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you are an intelligence agent,\Ncheck into it yourself. See ya. - OG}Faça como um agente de inteligência\Ne descubra sozinho. Falou!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.74,0:23:40.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey, wait! I'm not done talking! - OG}Ei, espera! Eu ainda estava falando com você!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.89,0:23:42.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Who do you think I am?! - OG}Sabe quem eu sou?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.91,0:23:47.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh, that... - OG}Ah, aquilo?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:52.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom did fulfill his promise\Nwith the Judicial Ship. - OG}O Tom cumpriu a promessa que fez\Nno navio judicial.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.16,0:23:56.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{His charge will probably be written off\Nin the trial that will be held in three days. - OG}As acusações devem ser retiradas\Nno julgamento daqui a três dias.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.01,0:23:58.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom is a great man. - OG}O Tom é um grande homem.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.41,0:24:00.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is ridiculous. - OG}Isso só pode ser brincadeira...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.92,0:24:04.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Such a serious charge related\Nto Roger will be written off? - OG}Vão retirar uma acusação séria dessas\Nrelacionada ao Roger?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.69,0:24:08.76,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Então algo assim realmente existe.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.76,0:24:09.81,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Sim, senhor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.81,0:24:12.91,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Naturally, there are pirates who're\Nsniffing around for these blueprints. - OG}Naturalmente, piratas também\Nestão procurando essas plantas.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.91,0:24:16.78,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{If, by chance, someone other than the\NGovernment got their hands on them, - OG}Na improvável hipótese de caírem\Nem mãos não-governamentais,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.78,0:24:20.06,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{there would no longer be any\Nmeans for us to fight against them. - OG}o governo não teria mais\Nchance de luta.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.06,0:24:24.18,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's been more than ten years since the\Ndawn of the so-called Great Pirate Era. - OG}Já faz dez anos desde o início\Nda chamada Grande Era da Pirataria.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.18,0:24:28.02,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Pirates have been gaining power quickly\Nand keep increasing in number. - OG}Os piratas ganharam poder rapidamente\Ne cresceram em número.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.02,0:24:32.89,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is no time for carefree talk about things like preventing the restoration of the ancient weapon! - OG}Não podemos ficar parados enquanto\Nas armas ancestrais são revividas!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.89,0:24:36.37,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Precisely because we uphold justice,\Nwe should have fangs like that! - OG}Nós, que defendemos a justiça,\Ndevemos possuir esse poder de fogo!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.37,0:24:41.54,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{We'll own the ancient weapon and repel this Great Pirate Era! - OG}Com a arma ancestral em nossas mãos,\Npodemos acabar com a Grande Era da Pirataria!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.33,0:24:47.54,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Times are changing.\NThere's some truth to what you said. - OG}Os tempos estão mudando. Você pode\Nter razão no que disse.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.54,0:24:52.92,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then obtain these blueprints you're talking about first. We'll discuss it further afterwards. - OG}Primeiro consiga essas plantas,\Ndepois conversamos mais.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.92,0:24:56.51,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{We'll leave this matter to you, Spandam. - OG}Deixamos esse assunto com você, Spandam.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.51,0:24:59.15,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yes, sir! Leave it to me, sir. - OG}Deixe comigo! Não vão se arrepender.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.06,0:25:04.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{After all my investigating,\NI finally got this chance! - OG}Depois de toda minha investigação, minha chance finalmente chegou!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.19,0:25:06.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não vou deixar escapar por nada!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.74,0:25:11.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.03,0:25:19.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Dammit! If he's not a criminal,\Nit'll be a problem for me! - OG}Droga! Se ele for absolvido, estou ferrado!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.99,0:25:21.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Spandam-san! - OG}– Agente Spandam!\N– Agente Spandam!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.33,0:25:30.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The hell with writing off the charge... - OG}Esqueça a absolvição...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.13,0:25:31.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How cocky... Just wait and see! - OG}Espera e vê, seu arrogante.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.88,0:25:36.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei! Chamem mais cinco agentes de inteligência!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.08,0:25:36.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Sim, senhor!\N– Sim, senhor!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.25,0:25:44.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Spandam-san! - OG}Agente Spandam!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.07,0:25:48.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Iceburg. Franky.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.78,0:25:49.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hm? - OG}Hã?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.45,0:25:51.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Both of you, come over here. - OG}Venham aqui um segundo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.65,0:25:54.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I wanna entrust something\Nimportant to you two. - OG}Preciso confiar algo importante a vocês.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.17,0:26:01.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{W-Why does something like this... - OG}P-Por que alguém projetaria algo assim?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.59,0:26:05.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{C-C-Can humans make something like this?! - OG}S-S-Seres humanos conseguem construir isso?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.33,0:26:09.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's the worst monster ever\Nin the history of shipbuilding. - OG}É a pior monstruosidade\Nna história da construção naval.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.29,0:26:13.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The Government has become aware of the existence of these blueprints and has started taking action. - OG}O governo descobriu sobre essas plantas\Ne já está agindo.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.53,0:26:15.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'd be dangerous to keep them with me. - OG}É perigoso demais ficarem comigo.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.80,0:26:20.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm scared... but I understand. We'll keep them. - OG}Estou com medo, mas...\NEntendo. Ficamos com elas.{Z/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.22,0:26:25.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is amazing! Hey, Iceburg,\Nlet's try building it! - OG}Que demais...!\NEi, Iceburg, vamos construir!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.10,0:26:26.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Seu idiota!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.28,0:26:28.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Ouch! - OG}Ai!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.39,0:26:30.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Think a little before you say things! - OG}Pensa antes de falar!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.34,0:26:32.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll keep them! - OG}Eu cuido delas.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.06,0:26:34.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If something like\Nthis is brought into this world... - OG}Se algo assim vier a existir...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.38,0:26:36.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hm? - OG}Hã?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.16,0:26:41.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah, the world will be finished. - OG}É, o mundo estaria perdido.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.37,0:26:50.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But now, you can do\Nwhatever you want with them. - OG}Enfim, agora é com vocês dois\No que fazem com elas.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.26,0:26:51.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You can even ditch them if it gets dangerous. - OG}Se ficar perigoso, destruam.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.96,0:26:53.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom-san... - OG}Tom...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.46,0:26:55.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{While I'm at it... - OG}Já que estamos aqui...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.06,0:26:58.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{...I'll tell you one more thing\Nthat I'm worried about. - OG}preciso contar mais uma coisa que me preocupa.{Gaijin}
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=23}===============================DIALOGUE============================
